categoriesPreview.name: Generative AI
categoriesPreview.description: Generative AI refers to a type of artificial intelligence that focuses on generating new, previously unseen content based on input data. This is accomplished through the use of generative models, such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) or Variational Autoencoders (VAEs), that are trained on a large dataset and then used to produce new examples that fit the characteristics of the data. This can be applied in a variety of domains, including image and music synthesis, natural language processing, and more.
